02:03:07.007 [agent:output] [coder] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PviopKjwtvPxPXj5fcZ46W","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a detailed exploration report.\n\n## ManuElearning Project Structure & Admin Quiz Stats Feature Exploration\n\n### 1. **Overall Project Structure**\n\n**Framework & Tech Stack:**\n- **Framework**: Astro 5.17.1 (static site generator with JavaScript components)\n- **Component Library**: Lit 3.3.2 (Web Components with LitElement)\n- **Database**: Firebase Firestore (NoSQL) with Firebase Authentication\n- **Styling**: CSS-in-JS via LitElement's `css` tagged template, custom variables\n- **Testing**: Vitest 4.0.18 with @testing-library/dom\n\n**Key Directories:**\n- `/src/pages/` - Astro route pages (.astro files)\n  - `/src/pages/admin/` - Admin panel pages (9 files: index, modules, quizzes, users, cohorts, sessions, questions, retention, settings)\n- `/src/components/` - Reusable Lit Web Components (.js files)\n- `/src/lib/firebase/` - Firebase service modules (16 files handling data access)\n- `/src/lib/` - Utility libraries (learning-path, retention, csv-export, search-filter, etc.)\n- `/src/layouts/` - Astro layout components\n- `/src/config/` - Configuration files\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Existing Admin Components & Pages**\n\nThe project has a well-established admin pattern with 9 admin pages:\n\n**Admin Pages:**\n- `/src/pages/admin/index.astro` - Main dashboard with shortcuts\n- `/src/pages/admin/modules.astro` - Module/lesson management\n- `/src/pages/admin/quizzes.astro` - Quiz management (already exists)\n- `/src/pages/admin/users.astro` - User management\n- `/src/pages/admin/cohorts.astro` - Convocatoria (cohort) management\n- `/src/pages/admin/sessions.astro` - Video session management\n- `/src/pages/admin/questions.astro` - Q&A questions management\n- `/src/pages/admin/retention.astro` - Retention dashboard\n- `/src/pages/admin/settings.astro` - Platform settings\n\n**Pattern:** Each admin page is a simple wrapper that imports a corresponding component from `/src/components/` and uses `AdminLayout`.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **How Modals & Expandable Sections Are Implemented**\n\n**Expandable Pattern** (from `admin-modules-list.js`):\n- Uses `_expandedModule` state property to track which item is open\n- Toggle function: `_toggleExpand(moduleId)` sets/unsets the expanded ID\n- CSS uses hidden/shown divs based on `isExpanded` conditional rendering\n- Smooth transitions with `transition: background 0.15s` on headers\n\n**Modal Pattern** (from `admin-modules-list.js`):\n- Fixed position overlay: `.form-overlay` with `position: fixed; inset: 0; background: rgba(0,0,0,0.4)`\n- Modal card inside: `.form-card` with `max-width: 520px`, `max-height: 90vh`, `overflow-y: auto`\n- Click outside closes: `@click=${this._closeForm}` on overlay with `@click=${(e) => e.stopPropagation()}` on card\n- Form validation before submission\n\n**Material Icons:**\n- Uses `material-symbols-outlined` from Google Material Icons\n- Imported via `materialIconsLink` from `shared/material-icons.js`\n- Icons: `expand_more`, `expand_less`, `add`, `edit`, `delete_outline`, `download`, etc.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **QuizResponses Firestore Collection Usage**\n\n**Collection Reference:**\n- Collection name: `quizResponses` (defined in `quizzes.js` line 17)\n- Firestore rules (lines 59-68 in `firestore.rules`):\n  - Users can read their own responses; admins can read all\n  - Signed-in users can create responses (userId must match auth.uid)\n  - Immutable: no updates or deletes allowed\n\n**Data Structure:**\n```javascript\n{\n  userId: string,         // Auto-validated to match auth.uid\n  quizId: string,         // Reference to the quiz\n  answers: string[],      // Array of answers (one per question)\n  completedAt: Timestamp  // Server timestamp\n}\n```\n\n**Firebase Functions Used:**\n- `getQuizResponses(quizId)` - Get all responses for a quiz (admin only)\n- `submitQuizResponse(userId, quizId, answers)` - Create a response\n- `getUserQuizResponse(userId, quizId)` - Get single user's response\n- `getUserQuizResults(userId)` - Get all user's quiz results with quiz details (joins with quizzes collection)\n\n**Current Usage in Admin:**\n- `admin-quizzes-list.js` calls `getQuizResponses(quizId)` to show responses in a panel\n- `quiz-results-view.js` (student view) calls `getUserQuizResults(userId)` to show their completed quizzes\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Firebase/Firestore Access Patterns**\n\n**Configuration** (`config.js`):\n- Initializes Firebase app with environment variables\n- Exports `auth` (getAuth) and `db` (getFirestore)\n\n**Service Module Pattern** (all files in `/src/lib/firebase/`):\n- Import Firestore functions from `firebase/firestore`\n- Import `db` from `config.js`\n- Consistent error handling: `try/catch` returns `{success: boolean, data/error}`\n- Validation functions before CRUD operations\n- Server-side timestamps for audit trails\n\n**Collections:**\n```\n- users\n- cohorts\n- modules\n  ├── lessons (subcollection per module)\n- quizzes\n- quizResponses\n- progress\n- questions\n- sessions\n- userNotifications\n- notifications\n- certificates\n- invitationCodes\n- settings\n- suggestedAnswers\n```\n\n**Query Patterns:**\n```javascript\n// Simple fetch all\nquery(ref, orderBy('field', 'asc'))\n\n// Conditional queries\nquery(ref, where('userId', '==', userId))\nquery(ref, where('completed', '==', true))\nquery(ref, where('role', '==', 'admin'))\n\n// Batch operations\nwriteBatch(db) with batch.update()\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Existing Quiz-Related Components & Data Models**\n\n**Quiz Data Model** (`quizzes.js`):\n```javascript\n{\n  id: string,\n  title: string,\n  moduleId: string,        // Required\n  lessonId: string,        // Optional\n  questions: {\n    text: string,\n    type: 'open' | 'multiple',\n    options: string[]       // Only for type='multiple'\n  }[],\n  createdAt: Timestamp\n}\n```\n\n**Components:**\n1. **`admin-quizzes-list.js`** (281 lines) - Full admin CRUD interface\n   - Create/edit/delete quizzes\n   - Form modal for quiz and question management\n   - Question builder with dynamic add/remove\n   - View responses expandable panel\n   - CSV export of responses\n   - State: `_quizzes`, `_viewingResponses`, `_responses`\n\n2. **`quiz-results-view.js`** (350 lines) - Student results display\n   - Shows completed quizzes per user\n   - Expandable detail view with Q&A\n   - Different rendering for open vs. multiple choice\n   - Badges and formatted dates\n   - State: `_results`, `_expandedQuiz`\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Admin Lesson List Component (Modules)**\n\n**File:** `/src/components/admin-modules-list.js` (847 lines)\n\n**Key Features:**\n- **Expandable modules:** Click module header to toggle lesson list\n- **Nested structure:** Modules contain lessons as subcollection\n- **CRUD operations:** Full module and lesson management\n- **Reordering:** Up/down buttons with `reorderModule()` and `reorderLesson()`\n- **Search:** `_searchQuery` state for filtering\n\n**State Management:**\n```javascript\n_modules: Array                 // All modules\n_expandedModule: String         // Currently expanded module ID\n_moduleLessons: Object          // Map of moduleId -> lessons array\n_showModuleForm: Boolean        // Form modal open\n_editingModuleId: String        // Which module being edited\n_moduleFormData: Object         // Form data\n_showLessonForm: Boolean        // Lesson form modal\n_lessonFormModuleId: String     // Parent module for lesson\n_lessonFormData: Object         // Lesson form data\n_searchQuery: String            // Search filter\n_notifyStudents: Boolean        // Notify on new module\n```\n\n**Header Structure:**\n```\nModule Card Header\n├── Reorder Buttons (up/down)\n├── Order Number Badge (#1, #2, etc)\n├── Module Title & Description\n├── Module Actions (Edit, Delete)\n└── Expand Toggle Icon\n\n[Expanded Content]\n├── Lessons Header with Count\n├── Add Lesson Button\n└── Lesson Items\n    ├── Reorder Buttons\n    ├── Order Circle Badge\n    ├── Lesson Title\n    ├── Meta Badges (Video, Docs)\n    └── Actions (Edit, Delete)\n```\n\n**Expandable Lessons Panel:**\n- Border-top separates from header\n- Light background (`#fafbfc`)\n- Lazy loads lessons on first expand via `fetchLessons(moduleId)`\n- Caches in `_moduleLessons` object\n\n**CSS Patterns:**\n- Modal overlay: `position: fixed; inset: 0; background: rgba(0,0,0,0.4); z-index: 100`\n- Cards: `box-shadow: 0 4px 6px -1px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.1); border-radius: 0.75rem`\n- Buttons: Primary (green gradient), Secondary (light gray), Danger (red)\n- Colors: Primary `#84cc16` (lime), Secondary `#fb923c` (orange), Text `#0f172a` (dark blue)\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Data Flow for Quiz Admin Features**\n\n**Currently Implemented (`admin-quizzes-list.js`):**\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ Admin Quizzes Page                          │\n│ (/admin/quizzes.astro)                      │\n└────────────────┬────────────────────────────┘\n                 │\n                 ▼\n        ┌──────────────────────┐\n        │ admin-quizzes-list   │\n        │ Web Component        │\n        └──────────┬───────────┘\n                   │\n         ┌─────────┴──────────┐\n         ▼                    ▼\n   ┌──────────────┐    ┌─────────────────┐\n   │ fetchAllQuizzes │  │ getQuizResponses│\n   │              │    │   (per quiz)    │\n   │ quizzes.js   │    └────────┬────────┘\n   └──────┬───────┘             │\n          │                     ▼\n          ▼               Quiz Responses List\n     Quizzes Array        (expandable panel)\n```\n\n**Current Quiz Card Display:**\n- Title\n- Question count\n- Module ID\n- Edit button\n- \"Respuestas\" (Responses) button - toggles response panel\n- Delete button\n- Response count (in panel)\n- CSV export button\n\n---\n\n### 9. **Key Implementation Patterns to Follow**\n\n**1. Component Structure:**\n```javascript\nexport class MyComponent extends LitElement {\n  static properties = { /* state properties */ };\n  static styles = css`{ /* BEM-style CSS */ }`;\n  \n  constructor() { /* initialize state */ }\n  connectedCallback() { /* load data */ }\n  \n  async _loadData() { /* with loading/error states */ }\n  _toggleExpand(id) { /* state management */ }\n  \n  render() { /* main template */ }\n  _renderItem(item) { /* sub-templates */ }\n  _renderForm() { /* form template */ }\n}\ncustomElements.define('my-component', MyComponent);\n```\n\n**2. Form Patterns:**\n- Modal overlay with close-on-outside-click\n- Form state separate from display state\n- Validation before submit\n- Success feedback reloads data\n- Error messages shown below form\n\n**3. Expandable/Collapse Patterns:**\n- Track expanded ID in state property\n- Toggle method flips the value\n- Conditional render checks `isExpanded === id`\n- Lazy-load data on first expand\n\n**4. Firebase Patterns:**\n```javascript\n// In service module:\nexport async function operation(params) {\n  try {\n    const result = await firebaseCall();\n    return { success: true, data: result };\n  } catch (err) {\n    return { success: false, error: 'User message' };\n  }\n}\n\n// In component:\nconst result = await operation(params);\nif (result.success) { /* use data */ }\nelse { this._error = result.error; }\n```\n\n---\n\n### 10. **File Paths Summary**\n\n**Key Files for Quiz Stats Feature:**\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/src/pages/admin/quizzes.astro` | Quiz admin page (wrapper) |\n| `/src/components/admin-quizzes-list.js` | Main quiz CRUD component |\n| `/src/lib/firebase/quizzes.js` | Quiz & response data service |\n| `/src/lib/firebase/modules.js` | Module & lesson data service |\n| `/src/lib/firebase/admin-stats.js` | Dashboard stats aggregator |\n| `/src/components/admin-modules-list.js` | Reference for expandable pattern |\n| `/src/components/quiz-results-view.js` | Reference for Q&A display pattern |\n| `firestore.rules` | Access control rules |\n| `/src/lib/firebase/config.js` | Firebase initialization |\n\n**Architecture Files:**\n- `/src/layouts/AdminLayout.astro` - Admin page wrapper/navigation\n- `/src/components/admin-dashboard.js` - Dashboard stats display\n- `/src/lib/csv-export.js` - CSV export utility\n\n---\n\nThis codebase is well-structured with clear separation of concerns: Astro pages for routing, Lit Web Components for UI, Firebase service modules for data access, and consistent patterns for modals, expandable sections, and form handling. The quiz feature already has the response collection set up and basic admin viewing, making it ready to extend with analytics and per-lesson statistics."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a80c300cea8ebdb47 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 97222\ntool_uses: 25\nduration_ms: 96139</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6dab462c-976e-4fe8-a358-d44adb2c1366","uuid":"c360b7ea-23a4-4bda-bcda-d7030ff833fe","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the manuelearning project to understand:\n1. Overall project structure (what framework, key directories)\n2. Existing admin components and pages - look for admin-related files\n3. How modals or expandable sections are implemented\n4. The quizResponses Firestore collection usage (any existing code referencing it)\n5. How Firebase/Firestore is accessed in the codebase\n6. Existing quiz-related components and data models\n7. The admin lesson list component specifically\n\nBe very thorough - check src/, components/, pages/, services/, etc. Look for patterns in how admin views load and display data.","agentId":"a80c300cea8ebdb47","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a detailed exploration report.\n\n## ManuElearning Project Structure & Admin Quiz Stats Feature Exploration\n\n### 1. **Overall Project Structure**\n\n**Framework & Tech Stack:**\n- **Framework**: Astro 5.17.1 (static site generator with JavaScript components)\n- **Component Library**: Lit 3.3.2 (Web Components with LitElement)\n- **Database**: Firebase Firestore (NoSQL) with Firebase Authentication\n- **Styling**: CSS-in-JS via LitElement's `css` tagged template, custom variables\n- **Testing**: Vitest 4.0.18 with @testing-library/dom\n\n**Key Directories:**\n- `/src/pages/` - Astro route pages (.astro files)\n  - `/src/pages/admin/` - Admin panel pages (9 files: index, modules, quizzes, users, cohorts, sessions, questions, retention, settings)\n- `/src/components/` - Reusable Lit Web Components (.js files)\n- `/src/lib/firebase/` - Firebase service modules (16 files handling data access)\n- `/src/lib/` - Utility libraries (learning-path, retention, csv-export, search-filter, etc.)\n- `/src/layouts/` - Astro layout components\n- `/src/config/` - Configuration files\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Existing Admin Components & Pages**\n\nThe project has a well-established admin pattern with 9 admin pages:\n\n**Admin Pages:**\n- `/src/pages/admin/index.astro` - Main dashboard with shortcuts\n- `/src/pages/admin/modules.astro` - Module/lesson management\n- `/src/pages/admin/quizzes.astro` - Quiz management (already exists)\n- `/src/pages/admin/users.astro` - User management\n- `/src/pages/admin/cohorts.astro` - Convocatoria (cohort) management\n- `/src/pages/admin/sessions.astro` - Video session management\n- `/src/pages/admin/questions.astro` - Q&A questions management\n- `/src/pages/admin/retention.astro` - Retention dashboard\n- `/src/pages/admin/settings.astro` - Platform settings\n\n**Pattern:** Each admin page is a simple wrapper that imports a corresponding component from `/src/components/` and uses `AdminLayout`.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **How Modals & Expandable Sections Are Implemented**\n\n**Expandable Pattern** (from `admin-modules-list.js`):\n- Uses `_expandedModule` state property to track which item is open\n- Toggle function: `_toggleExpand(moduleId)` sets/unsets the expanded ID\n- CSS uses hidden/shown divs based on `isExpanded` conditional rendering\n- Smooth transitions with `transition: background 0.15s` on headers\n\n**Modal Pattern** (from `admin-modules-list.js`):\n- Fixed position overlay: `.form-overlay` with `position: fixed; inset: 0; background: rgba(0,0,0,0.4)`\n- Modal card inside: `.form-card` with `max-width: 520px`, `max-height: 90vh`, `overflow-y: auto`\n- Click outside closes: `@click=${this._closeForm}` on overlay with `@click=${(e) => e.stopPropagation()}` on card\n- Form validation before submission\n\n**Material Icons:**\n- Uses `material-symbols-outlined` from Google Material Icons\n- Imported via `materialIconsLink` from `shared/material-icons.js`\n- Icons: `expand_more`, `expand_less`, `add`, `edit`, `delete_outline`, `download`, etc.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **QuizResponses Firestore Collection Usage**\n\n**Collection Reference:**\n- Collection name: `quizResponses` (defined in `quizzes.js` line 17)\n- Firestore rules (lines 59-68 in `firestore.rules`):\n  - Users can read their own responses; admins can read all\n  - Signed-in users can create responses (userId must match auth.uid)\n  - Immutable: no updates or deletes allowed\n\n**Data Structure:**\n```javascript\n{\n  userId: string,         // Auto-validated to match auth.uid\n  quizId: string,         // Reference to the quiz\n  answers: string[],      // Array of answers (one per question)\n  completedAt: Timestamp  // Server timestamp\n}\n```\n\n**Firebase Functions Used:**\n- `getQuizResponses(quizId)` - Get all responses for a quiz (admin only)\n- `submitQuizResponse(userId, quizId, answers)` - Create a response\n- `getUserQuizResponse(userId, quizId)` - Get single user's response\n- `getUserQuizResults(userId)` - Get all user's quiz results with quiz details (joins with quizzes collection)\n\n**Current Usage in Admin:**\n- `admin-quizzes-list.js` calls `getQuizResponses(quizId)` to show responses in a panel\n- `quiz-results-view.js` (student view) calls `getUserQuizResults(userId)` to show their completed quizzes\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Firebase/Firestore Access Patterns**\n\n**Configuration** (`config.js`):\n- Initializes Firebase app with environment variables\n- Exports `auth` (getAuth) and `db` (getFirestore)\n\n**Service Module Pattern** (all files in `/src/lib/firebase/`):\n- Import Firestore functions from `firebase/firestore`\n- Import `db` from `config.js`\n- Consistent error handling: `try/catch` returns `{success: boolean, data/error}`\n- Validation functions before CRUD operations\n- Server-side timestamps for audit trails\n\n**Collections:**\n```\n- users\n- cohorts\n- modules\n  ├── lessons (subcollection per module)\n- quizzes\n- quizResponses\n- progress\n- questions\n- sessions\n- userNotifications\n- notifications\n- certificates\n- invitationCodes\n- settings\n- suggestedAnswers\n```\n\n**Query Patterns:**\n```javascript\n// Simple fetch all\nquery(ref, orderBy('field', 'asc'))\n\n// Conditional queries\nquery(ref, where('userId', '==', userId))\nquery(ref, where('completed', '==', true))\nquery(ref, where('role', '==', 'admin'))\n\n// Batch operations\nwriteBatch(db) with batch.update()\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Existing Quiz-Related Components & Data Models**\n\n**Quiz Data Model** (`quizzes.js`):\n```javascript\n{\n  id: string,\n  title: string,\n  moduleId: string,        // Required\n  lessonId: string,        // Optional\n  questions: {\n    text: string,\n    type: 'open' | 'multiple',\n    options: string[]       // Only for type='multiple'\n  }[],\n  createdAt: Timestamp\n}\n```\n\n**Components:**\n1. **`admin-quizzes-list.js`** (281 lines) - Full admin CRUD interface\n   - Create/edit/delete quizzes\n   - Form modal for quiz and question management\n   - Question builder with dynamic add/remove\n   - View responses expandable panel\n   - CSV export of responses\n   - State: `_quizzes`, `_viewingResponses`, `_responses`\n\n2. **`quiz-results-view.js`** (350 lines) - Student results display\n   - Shows completed quizzes per user\n   - Expandable detail view with Q&A\n   - Different rendering for open vs. multiple choice\n   - Badges and formatted dates\n   - State: `_results`, `_expandedQuiz`\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Admin Lesson List Component (Modules)**\n\n**File:** `/src/components/admin-modules-list.js` (847 lines)\n\n**Key Features:**\n- **Expandable modules:** Click module header to toggle lesson list\n- **Nested structure:** Modules contain lessons as subcollection\n- **CRUD operations:** Full module and lesson management\n- **Reordering:** Up/down buttons with `reorderModule()` and `reorderLesson()`\n- **Search:** `_searchQuery` state for filtering\n\n**State Management:**\n```javascript\n_modules: Array                 // All modules\n_expandedModule: String         // Currently expanded module ID\n_moduleLessons: Object          // Map of moduleId -> lessons array\n_showModuleForm: Boolean        // Form modal open\n_editingModuleId: String        // Which module being edited\n_moduleFormData: Object         // Form data\n_showLessonForm: Boolean        // Lesson form modal\n_lessonFormModuleId: String     // Parent module for lesson\n_lessonFormData: Object         // Lesson form data\n_searchQuery: String            // Search filter\n_notifyStudents: Boolean        // Notify on new module\n```\n\n**Header Structure:**\n```\nModule Card Header\n├── Reorder Buttons (up/down)\n├── Order Number Badge (#1, #2, etc)\n├── Module Title & Description\n├── Module Actions (Edit, Delete)\n└── Expand Toggle Icon\n\n[Expanded Content]\n├── Lessons Header with Count\n├── Add Lesson Button\n└── Lesson Items\n    ├── Reorder Buttons\n    ├── Order Circle Badge\n    ├── Lesson Title\n    ├── Meta Badges (Video, Docs)\n    └── Actions (Edit, Delete)\n```\n\n**Expandable Lessons Panel:**\n- Border-top separates from header\n- Light background (`#fafbfc`)\n- Lazy loads lessons on first expand via `fetchLessons(moduleId)`\n- Caches in `_moduleLessons` object\n\n**CSS Patterns:**\n- Modal overlay: `position: fixed; inset: 0; background: rgba(0,0,0,0.4); z-index: 100`\n- Cards: `box-shadow: 0 4px 6px -1px rgb(0 0 0 / 0.1); border-radius: 0.75rem`\n- Buttons: Primary (green gradient), Secondary (light gray), Danger (red)\n- Colors: Primary `#84cc16` (lime), Secondary `#fb923c` (orange), Text `#0f172a` (dark blue)\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Data Flow for Quiz Admin Features**\n\n**Currently Implemented (`admin-quizzes-list.js`):**\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ Admin Quizzes Page                          │\n│ (/admin/quizzes.astro)                      │\n└────────────────┬────────────────────────────┘\n                 │\n                 ▼\n        ┌──────────────────────┐\n        │ admin-quizzes-list   │\n        │ Web Component        │\n        └──────────┬───────────┘\n                   │\n         ┌─────────┴──────────┐\n         ▼                    ▼\n   ┌──────────────┐    ┌─────────────────┐\n   │ fetchAllQuizzes │  │ getQuizResponses│\n   │              │    │   (per quiz)    │\n   │ quizzes.js   │    └────────┬────────┘\n   └──────┬───────┘             │\n          │                     ▼\n          ▼               Quiz Responses List\n     Quizzes Array        (expandable panel)\n```\n\n**Current Quiz Card Display:**\n- Title\n- Question count\n- Module ID\n- Edit button\n- \"Respuestas\" (Responses) button - toggles response panel\n- Delete button\n- Response count (in panel)\n- CSV export button\n\n---\n\n### 9. **Key Implementation Patterns to Follow**\n\n**1. Component Structure:**\n```javascript\nexport class MyComponent extends LitElement {\n  static properties = { /* state properties */ };\n  static styles = css`{ /* BEM-style CSS */ }`;\n  \n  constructor() { /* initialize state */ }\n  connectedCallback() { /* load data */ }\n  \n  async _loadData() { /* with loading/error states */ }\n  _toggleExpand(id) { /* state management */ }\n  \n  render() { /* main template */ }\n  _renderItem(item) { /* sub-templates */ }\n  _renderForm() { /* form template */ }\n}\ncustomElements.define('my-component', MyComponent);\n```\n\n**2. Form Patterns:**\n- Modal overlay with close-on-outside-click\n- Form state separate from display state\n- Validation before submit\n- Success feedback reloads data\n- Error messages shown below form\n\n**3. Expandable/Collapse Patterns:**\n- Track expanded ID in state property\n- Toggle method flips the value\n- Conditional render checks `isExpanded === id`\n- Lazy-load data on first expand\n\n**4. Firebase Patterns:**\n```javascript\n// In service module:\nexport async function operation(params) {\n  try {\n    const result = await firebaseCall();\n    return { success: true, data: result };\n  } catch (err) {\n    return { success: false, error: 'User message' };\n  }\n}\n\n// In component:\nconst result = await operation(params);\nif (result.success) { /* use data */ }\nelse { this._error = result.error; }\n```\n\n---\n\n### 10. **File Paths Summary**\n\n**Key Files for Quiz Stats Feature:**\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/src/pages/admin/quizzes.astro` | Quiz admin page (wrapper) |\n| `/src/components/admin-quizzes-list.js` | Main quiz CRUD component |\n| `/src/lib/firebase/quizzes.js` | Quiz & response data service |\n| `/src/lib/firebase/modules.js` | Module & lesson data service |\n| `/src/lib/firebase/admin-stats.js` | Dashboard stats aggregator |\n| `/src/components/admin-modules-list.js` | Reference for expandable pattern |\n| `/src/components/quiz-results-view.js` | Reference for Q&A display pattern |\n| `firestore.rules` | Access control rules |\n| `/src/lib/firebase/config.js` | Firebase initialization |\n\n**Architecture Files:**\n- `/src/layouts/AdminLayout.astro` - Admin page wrapper/navigation\n- `/src/components/admin-dashboard.js` - Dashboard stats display\n- `/src/lib/csv-export.js` - CSV export utility\n\n---\n\nThis codebase is well-structured with clear separation of concerns: Astro pages for routing, Lit Web Components for UI, Firebase service modules for data access, and consistent patterns for modals, expandable sections, and form handling. The quiz feature already has the response collection set up and basic admin viewing, making it ready to extend with analytics and per-lesson statistics."}],"totalDurationMs":96139,"totalTokens":97222,"totalToolUseCount":25,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":552,"cache_read_input_tokens":93045,"output_tokens":3625,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":552},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}} (stream=stdout)
