02:09:18.433 [agent:output] [coder] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JkAY4iRZBT4gU6S9PgBH7M","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile the comprehensive report.\n\n## Codebase Exploration Report - ManuElearning Quiz Stats Feature\n\n### 1. Admin Components Found\nAll files located in `/home/manu/ws_firebase/manuelearning/src/components/`:\n\n- `admin-guard.js` (96 lines) - Authentication guard\n- `admin-notifications-badge.js` (70 lines) - Notification indicator\n- `admin-dashboard.js` (260 lines) - Main dashboard\n- `admin-users-list.js` (333 lines) - User management\n- `admin-sessions-list.js` (327 lines) - Session tracking\n- `admin-questions-list.js` (227 lines) - Question management\n- `admin-cohorts-list.js` (746 lines) - Cohort/convocatoria management\n- `admin-modules-list.js` (846 lines) - Module & lesson management\n- `admin-retention-dashboard.js` (165 lines) - Retention analytics\n- `admin-quizzes-list.js` (554 lines) - Quiz management and statistics\n\n### 2. Quiz-Related Files\n\n**Main File: `/home/manu/ws_firebase/manuelearning/src/lib/firebase/quizzes.js`**\n\nDatabase collections used:\n- `quizzes` - Quiz definitions (title, moduleId, lessonId, questions array, createdAt)\n- `quizResponses` - User responses to quizzes (userId, quizId, answers array, completedAt)\n\nKey exports:\n- `fetchAllQuizzes()` - Get all quizzes ordered by creation date\n- `fetchQuiz(id)` - Get single quiz\n- `createQuiz(data)` - Create new quiz\n- `updateQuiz(id, updates)` - Update quiz\n- `deleteQuiz(id)` - Delete quiz\n- `submitQuizResponse(userId, quizId, answers)` - Save user's response\n- `getUserQuizResponse(userId, quizId)` - Get specific user response\n- `getQuizResponses(quizId)` - Get all responses for a quiz (admin view)\n- `getUserQuizResults(userId)` - Get all quiz results for user with quiz details\n\n### 3. Quiz Response Code Locations\n\n**Reference in `admin-quizzes-list.js`:**\n- Line 7: `getQuizResponses` imported\n- Lines 29-31: Response viewing state (`_viewingResponses`, `_responses`)\n- Lines 236-241: `_toggleResponses()` method - fetches responses via `getQuizResponses()`\n- Lines 243-292: `_openStats()` method - loads responses and builds statistics\n- Line 288: Data structure includes `responses` array with user responses\n\n**Firestore collection:** `quizResponses` (18 references in code across multiple files)\n\n### 4. Admin Quizzes List Component - Full Structure\n\n**File:** `/home/manu/ws_firebase/manuelearning/src/components/admin-quizzes-list.js` (554 lines)\n\n**Key State Properties:**\n- `_quizzes` - Array of quiz objects\n- `_loading` - Loading state\n- `_error` - Error messages\n- `_showForm` - Create/edit form modal visibility\n- `_editingId` - Current editing quiz ID\n- `_formData` - Form data with title, moduleId, lessonId, questions\n- `_viewingResponses` - Quiz ID being viewed for responses\n- `_responses` - Array of quiz responses\n- `_showStats` - Current quiz for stats modal\n- `_statsLoading` - Stats loading state\n- `_statsData` - Processed statistics data\n- `_usersMap` - Map of userId to display names (for stats)\n\n**Key Methods:**\n1. `_loadQuizzes()` - Fetches all quizzes\n2. `_openCreate()` / `_openEdit(quiz)` - Opens form modal\n3. `_toggleResponses(quizId)` - Toggles response panel visibility\n4. `_openStats(quiz)` - Opens stats modal with processed data\n5. `_closeStats()` - Closes stats modal\n6. `_exportResponses(quiz)` - Exports stats to CSV\n\n**Stats Calculation (lines 243-292):**\n- Fetches quiz responses\n- Fetches all users and builds name map\n- For multiple-choice questions: Tracks option distribution, correctness counts\n- For open-ended: Counts total answers\n- Calculates: total responses, correct/incorrect percentages per question\n- Groups responses by student with answer details\n\n**CSV Export (lines 223-234):**\n- Headers: Usuario, Fecha, Pregunta 1, Pregunta 2, etc.\n- Rows: User name, completion date, answers per question\n\n**Modal Patterns Used:**\n- `.form-overlay` - Fixed position backdrop with 40% black opacity (line 62)\n- `.form-card` - Centered white card, max 560px width, shadow, scrollable (line 63)\n- Click outside card dismisses modal (event propagation stop)\n- H3 title, form groups, error messages, action buttons at bottom\n\n### 5. User Fetching Pattern\n\n**File:** `/home/manu/ws_firebase/manuelearning/src/lib/firebase/users.js`\n\n**Function:** `fetchAllUsers()`\n```javascript\nexport async function fetchAllUsers() {\n  const usersRef = collection(db, 'users');\n  const q = query(usersRef, orderBy('createdAt', 'desc'));\n  const snapshot = await getDocs(q);\n  return { success: true, users };  // Returns array with uid, displayName, email, role, etc.\n}\n```\n\nReturns object: `{ success: boolean, users?: UserProfile[], error?: string }`\n\nUser properties: `uid`, `email`, `displayName`, `role` ('student'|'admin'), `cohortId`, `createdAt`\n\n**Usage in admin-quizzes-list.js (line 250):**\n```javascript\nconst [responsesResult, usersResult] = await Promise.all([\n  getQuizResponses(quiz.id),\n  Object.keys(this._usersMap).length === 0 ? fetchAllUsers() : Promise.resolve(null),\n]);\n```\n- Fetches users only once (cached in `_usersMap`)\n- Maps userId -> displayName for stats display\n\n### 6. Project Structure\n\n**Root directories:**\n```\n/src/\n  ├── components/          (26+ component files including 10 admin components)\n  ├── lib/                 (config, utilities, Firebase services)\n  │   ├── firebase/        (16 service files: auth, users, quizzes, modules, etc.)\n  │   ├── auth-ready.js\n  │   ├── csv-export.js\n  │   ├── search-filter.js\n  ├── pages/               (Astro pages for routing)\n  │   ├── admin/           (dashboard, quizzes.astro, users.astro, modules.astro, etc.)\n  │   ├── login.astro\n  │   ├── dashboard.astro\n  │   ├── leccion.astro\n  ├── layouts/             (Page layouts)\n  ├── config/              (Configuration files)\n  └── styles/              (Global styles)\n```\n\n**Pages directory structure:**\n```\n/pages/\n  ├── admin/\n  │   ├── index.astro\n  │   ├── dashboard.astro (aggregate stats)\n  │   ├── quizzes.astro (component: admin-quizzes-list)\n  │   ├── users.astro\n  │   ├── modules.astro\n  │   ├── sessions.astro\n  │   ├── cohorts.astro\n  │   ├── questions.astro\n  │   ├── settings.astro\n  │   └── retention.astro\n  └── [public pages: login, curso, leccion, resultados, sesiones, perfil, etc.]\n```\n\n### 7. Modal Pattern Summary\n\nAll admin components use consistent modal overlay pattern:\n\n**CSS Classes:**\n- `.form-overlay` - Fixed backdrop, 100% coverage, centered flex container\n- `.form-card` - White card, max-width varies (520px-700px), scrollable\n- `.form-group` - Input wrapper with label, margin-bottom: 1rem\n- `.form-actions` - Button container, flex row, bottom of form\n- `.form-error` - Error text display, red color\n\n**Rendering Pattern (Lit):**\n```javascript\n_renderForm() {\n  return html`\n    <div class=\"form-overlay\" @click=${this._closeForm}>\n      <div class=\"form-card\" @click=${(e) => e.stopPropagation()}>\n        <h3>${title}</h3>\n        <form @submit=${this._handleSubmit}>\n          <!-- form groups -->\n        </form>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  `;\n}\n```\n\n### 8. Admin Stats Integration\n\n**File:** `/home/manu/ws_firebase/manuelearning/src/lib/firebase/admin-stats.js`\n\nProvides dashboard-level statistics:\n- `countTotalUsers()` - Total registered users\n- `countActiveUsersLast7Days()` - Active users from progress collection\n- `countQuizzesCompleted()` - Count of all quizResponses documents\n- `getProgressByCohort()` - Average progress per cohort\n- `fetchAdminDashboardStats()` - All stats in one call\n\nThe quiz statistics in admin-quizzes-list.js are more granular (per quiz, per question, per student).\n\n---\n\nAll admin components follow the same architec